# learndl — Project-specific rules

## Project overview
Quantitative research and trading strategy development for equities: data acquisition, factor research, backtesting, risk analysis, and simulation trading.

## Typical layout (confirm by browsing)
```
├── pyproject.toml        # metadata & dependencies
├── .gitignore
├── configs/              # settings, defaults, model params
├── src/                  # application / library source
├── scripts/              # purpose-specific Python scripts
├── runs/                 # .bat / .sh helpers
├── resources/            # shared code resources
├── templates/            # html / css / img / font
├── data/                 # raw & processed (usually not synced)
├── models/               # exported models (usually not synced)
├── results/              # exports (usually not synced)
├── logs/                 # logs (usually not synced)
├── .local_resources/     # local-only assets (not synced)
└── .secret/              # secrets (not synced)
```

## Default toolchain
- **Primary table library:** Prefer **pandas** unless performance requires **polars**.
- **HTTP / async:** For new network clients, prefer **curl_cffi**.

## Logging
Use the project logger: `src.proj.Logger`.

## Data and factors
- Correctness first; re-verify when changing data paths or transforms.
- Prefer vectorization, threading, or heavier libs (e.g. torch, polars) when it clearly pays off.
- Raw/processed data: use existing pipelines — `src.proj.DB` for raw, `src.data.DATAVENDOR` (and related loaders) for processed data as documented in code.
- Factors: follow patterns under `src.res.factor` (e.g. `util/classes`, vectorized calculators).
- Respect existing cleaning choices (e.g. forward-fill, winsorization, neutralization).

## Backtesting and strategies
- Model costs and rules like existing strategies: commission, slippage, stamp duty, limits, suspensions.
- No lookahead: only information available at decision time.

## Docs
- Update README or operator docs when behavior or setup changes for users of this repo.

## Data fetching policy
- Ask the human before any new external scrape or new data provider.

## Repository hygiene
- Do not suggest committing paths under `.local_resources/` or `.secret/` to git.

## Post-edit checks (substantive code changes)
- `ruff check src scripts`
- `pyright src scripts`
